            <h3>BlurFilter</h3>
            <p>BlurFilter is a class that stores information about blur effects. Objects can be generated by specifying the value of each property in the constructor arguments, or by default with no arguments, and only properties that need to be changed are reassigned.</p>
            <p class="tutorial-image"><img src="<%= path %>assets/img/tutorial/blur.svg" alt="BlurFilter image"></p>

            <p>
              <ul>
                <li>blurX: The amount of horizontal blur.</li>
                <li>blurY: The amount of vertical blur.</li>
                <li>quality: The number of times to perform the blur.</li>
              </ul>
            </p>

            <h5>Example</h5>
            <p><pre>const {BlurFilter} = next2d.filters;
const {Shape} = next2d.display;

const shape = new Shape();
shape
    .graphics
    .beginFill()
    .drawRect(0, 0, 50, 50);

shape.filters = [new BlurFilter()];
this.addChild(shape);</pre></p>

